3. AUTHENTICATION LAYER

ECH Handshake Protocol

Required at:

* Session initiation
* API request
* Ledger mutation
* Settlement routing
* User auth
* Cloud shell execution
* Telnet terminal access
* Wallet binding

Sequence:

Client Init
  ->
ECH HELLO
  ->
Public Key Exchange
  ->
Merkle Root Verification
  ->
Session Token
  ->
Dynamic Routing Auth
  ->
Execution Permission

Components:

* TLS + ECH
* Merkle Root Hash
* Device fingerprint
* Treasury signature
* FICO / risk policy
* Session nonce
* Dynamic key rotation

